    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-02-08T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-02-08T14:00:00-05:00" n="38"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.4016/2–847: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Italy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-02-08T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 8, 1947—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>190. In concert your Brit colleague<note n="1" xml:id="d38fn1">Sir Noel
                        Charles.</note> you shd inform Ital Govt <gloss target="#t_SAC1">SAC</gloss>
                    has been directed (<gloss target="#t_Fan1">Fan</gloss> 724<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d38fn2">
                        <gloss target="#t_WARX1">WARX</gloss> 91618, February 8, not
                    printed.</note>) to lend all practicable assistance Ital authorities to
                    facilitate measures expedite evacuation Itals wishing leave Pola with their
                    personal possessions.</p>
                <p>You shd also state that although Allied personnel cannot actively assist in
                    removal industrial plant and equipment from Pola, they will place no obstacle in
                    way of Itals desiring move such property to another location in Zone A if they
                    can make necessary arrangements.</p>
                <p>Further you shd confirm to Ital Govt Allied troops will remain Pola until treaty
                    comes into force.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
